article.description: Ryan Richardson scored 17 points, Joel Bolomboy had 12 points and 16 rebounds, and Weber State roughed up Southern Utah 77-50 on Saturday night.
article.headline: Weber State roughs up Southern Utah 77-50
article.linkText: Weber State roughs up Southern Utah 77-50
article.story: OGDEN, Utah -- Ryan Richardson scored 17 points, Joel Bolomboy had 12 points and 16 rebounds, and Weber State roughed up Southern Utah 77-50 on Saturday night. Bolomboy is second in the nation with 13.3 rebounds per game and notched his 19th double-double in 21 games for Weber State (15-6, 7-1 Big Sky). He's tied with New Mexico State's Pascal Siakam for the most double-doubles in college basketball. Richardson made 4 of 5 3-pointers and 5 of 7 overall. Southern Utah (4-15, 2-7) started 3 of 15 from the field and finished the first half shooting 25 percent and trailing 45-16. The Thunderbirds tied a season low with three 3-pointers made. Weber State has won two in a row after suffering its first conference loss to Idaho State in a 69-68 buzzer-beating defeat last Saturday.
